{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "qa-technical-assessment",
    "name": "QA Technical Assessment",
    "description": "API test collection for JSONPlaceholder endpoints (https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com) as part of the QA Engineer Technical Assessment.\n\nThis collection covers 4 API endpoints with positive tests, response validation, and at least 1 negative/edge case per endpoint.\n\nEndpoints tested:\n- GET /users (retrieve all users)\n- GET /users/:id (retrieve specific user)\n- POST /posts (create a new post)\n- PUT /posts/:id (update an existing post)\n- DELETE /posts/:id (delete a post)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "GET Users",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get All Users",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["jsonplaceholder", "typicode", "com"],
              "path": ["users"]
            },
            "description": "## Request Details\n- **Method:** GET\n- **Endpoint:** /users\n- **Parameters:** None\n- **Authentication:** None required\n\n## Expected Response\n- **Status Code:** 200 OK\n- **Body:** JSON array of 10 user objects\n- **Each user contains:** id, name, username, email, address, phone, website, company\n\n## Analysis\nThis endpoint returns all users from the mock database. JSONPlaceholder always returns exactly 10 users. The response includes nested objects (address with geo coordinates, company with catchPhrase). Response time should be under 2 seconds. No pagination is implemented — the full dataset is returned in a single response."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 - All Users Retrieved Successfully",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users",
                  "protocol": "https",
                  "host": ["jsonplaceholder", "typicode", "com"],
                  "path": ["users"]
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json; charset=utf-8" },
                { "key": "Cache-Control", "value": "max-age=43200" }
              ],
              "body": "[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"name\": \"Leanne Graham\",\n    \"username\": \"Bret\",\n    \"email\": \"Sincere@april.biz\",\n    \"address\": {\n      \"street\": \"Kulas Light\",\n      \"suite\": \"Apt. 556\",\n      \"city\": \"Gwenborough\",\n      \"zipcode\": \"92998-3874\",\n      \"geo\": { \"lat\": \"-37.3159\", \"lng\": \"81.1496\" }\n    },\n    \"phone\": \"1-770-736-8031 x56442\",\n    \"website\": \"hildegard.org\",\n    \"company\": {\n      \"name\": \"Romaguera-Crona\",\n      \"catchPhrase\": \"Multi-layered client-server neural-net\",\n      \"bs\": \"harness real-time e-markets\"\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 2,\n    \"name\": \"Ervin Howell\",\n    \"username\": \"Antonette\",\n    \"email\": \"Shanna@melissa.tv\"\n  }\n]"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response time is under 2 seconds', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(2000);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is application/json', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/json');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response is an array of 10 users', function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.length).to.eql(10);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Each user has required fields', function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    jsonData.forEach(function(user) {",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('id');",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('name');",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('email');",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('username');",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('address');",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('phone');",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('website');",
                  "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property('company');",
                  "    });",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('User IDs are sequential from 1 to 10', function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    jsonData.forEach(function(user, index) {",
                  "        pm.expect(user.id).to.eql(index + 1);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Edge Case - Get Users with Invalid Query Param",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users?id=invalid",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["jsonplaceholder", "typicode", "com"],
              "path": ["users"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "id",
                  "value": "invalid"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "## Request Details\n- **Method:** GET\n- **Endpoint:** /users?id=invalid\n- **Parameters:** id=invalid (non-numeric value)\n\n## Expected Response\n- **Status Code:** 200 OK\n- **Body:** Empty JSON array []\n\n## Analysis\nNegative test: passing a non-numeric string as the id filter parameter. JSONPlaceholder does not return a 400 Bad Request for invalid query params — instead it returns 200 with an empty array. This is a design observation: the API silently filters with no matches rather than rejecting invalid input. A production API should ideally return 400 for malformed parameters."
          },
