            "description": "## Request Details\n- **Method:** POST\n- **Endpoint:** /posts\n- **Headers:** Content-Type: application/json\n- **Body:** { title, body, userId }\n\n## Expected Response\n- **Status Code:** 201 Created\n- **Body:** Created post object with server-assigned id (101)\n- **Fields returned:** id, title, body, userId\n\n## Analysis\nThis endpoint simulates creating a new resource. JSONPlaceholder always assigns id: 101 to new posts (since 100 posts exist in the mock database). The server echoes back the submitted data plus the generated id. Important: this is a mock API — the post is not actually persisted. Subsequent GET requests will not return this post. The Content-Type header must be set to application/json for the server to parse the body correctly."
