            },
            "description": "## Request Details\n- **Method:** PUT\n- **Endpoint:** /posts/1\n- **Path Parameter:** id = 1\n- **Headers:** Content-Type: application/json\n- **Body:** { title: 'Updated Post', body: 'Updated content', userId: 1 }\n\n## Expected Response\n- **Status Code:** 200 OK\n- **Body:** Updated post object with id: 1 and the new field values\n\n## Analysis\nPUT performs a full resource replacement. The server returns the updated object with id preserved. JSONPlaceholder simulates the update — calling GET /posts/1 afterward will still return the original data since this is a mock API. In a production environment, PUT should replace all fields; omitted fields would be removed (unlike PATCH which is partial). The response confirms the update was accepted by echoing back the submitted data."
          },
